In this world view, a system is visualized as consisting of discrete units of traffic that move (“flow”) from point to point in the system while com-peting with each other for the use of scarce resources. The units of traffic are sometimes called “transactions,” giving rise to the phrase “transaction flow.” Numerous systems fit the preceding description.
